subSubSection.paragraph:
Distribution and habitat. Specimens were collected from Cauaçu Farm, João Câmara, Caatinga phytogeographic domain, within a semiarid landscape of about 700 ha with secondary forested and wide open areas. The specimens were found over top soil and dead foliage coverage and were collected with entomological aspirators. The climate of the region is “As” following the Köppen-Geiger climate classification, which means an equatorial main climate with dry summer (
Kottek et al. 2006
). The average annual rainfall is 648.6 mm , with average annual temperature of 24.7 °C (
Ferreira et al. 2018
).
